working with challenging behaviour whilst pregnant i'm weeks pregnant work fulltime as a support worker for clients that require hour nursing care display challenging behavior the company is currently short staffed therefore i've been made to work with these clients with just one other staff member i'm very concerned for the health safety of myself my baby as i feel it's greatly putting my child at risk if a client displays violence or aggression there are not enough people on shift to help which could cause serious injury to myself my baby not to mention i'm exhausted from so much work especially because i have to work days solid before getting a day off i did have a risk assessment at the start of my pregnancy but my manager didn't go through this with me she did it all herself i have asked on several occasions for another assessment as circumstances in the workplace have changed this has not been done i've spoken to my manager about my concerns she told me i'd have to cope am i right to be concerned i also rang citizen's advice this morning but they wern't much help i was told that they couldn't really see and issue and they asked me if it was just because i wanted some time off work i feel like nobody is listneing or taking me seriously you have every right to be concerned when i was pregnant with my youngest son who is now i was asked if i would like to do some work with disabled children but once it was explained to me the situation and what i would be doing and dealing with i decided not to as if anything happened to my unborn child i would never be able to forgive myself Pregnancy Breastfeeding Abortion debate Abortion Abortion in the United States Childbirth Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Miscarriage Knots Landing Strategic management EastEnders Health insurance Cytomegalovirus Prostate cancer Wal-Mart Workplace democracy Teenage pregnancy Milton H. Erickson Clinical depression Nurse Cornelia Rau Psychotherapy Fathers' rights Hillary Rodham C